Label: XML
Comment: "Subscribers can use respective carrier's IDD when calling abroad. We have not configured\nany preferredInternationalPrefix as there is no official evidence for it."

Label: XML_FIXED_LINE
Comment: "Numbers online have been found that start with 20, despite the ITU doc not covering\nthese."

Label: XML_MOBILE
Comment:
"Numbers found online starting with 62 and 64. 14, 63 and 65 are from an open-source bug
report, we couldn't find evidence of these specifically being in use but this article
http://www.prachachat.net/news_detail.php?newsid=1395732787 talks about prefix 6 and 1
being cleared for mobile use."

Label: XML_TOLL_FREE
Comment: "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toll-free_telephone_number. Prefix 001800 of length\n13-digit is added based on user report."

Label: XML_VOIP
Comment: "The ITU document says that the 89 prefix is also VOIP but there are lots of numbers\nonline to suggest they are actually used as mobile numbers."
